The FCS-MPCC algorithm flow is presented in Fig.Â 9, and the structure of FCS-MPCC for the PV inverter is shown in Fig.Â 10. The details of the control strategy mainly include the following 6 parts:
The measurement module. Through real-time measurements of grid voltages, inverter currents and DC bus voltages, the actual operating data is transmitted to the prediction model.
PLL. PLL provides the phase angle for coordinate transformation and calculation of the prediction model.
Prediction model. The prediction model uses the recursive relationship in (17) to calculate the current prediction value at k+1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$k + 1$$\end{document} time through the measured value of the system at k\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$k$$\end{document} time.
Optimize the value function. The quadratic error of the reference current and the predicted current at k+1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$k + 1$$\end{document} time is taken as the optimization value function in (18).
Current reference. The active current reference comes from the outer DC voltage loop, i.e., the reference voltage Udcref\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$U_{{{\text{dcref}}}}$$\end{document} of the PV module is generated by MPPT control, and is then compared to the measured DC bus voltage Udc\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$U_{{{\text{dc}}}}$$\end{document}, before passing to a PI regulator. In order to be connected to the power grid with unit power factor, the reactive current reference is set to 0.
Signal driver. From the optimized value function, the switch state corresponding to the minimum value function is taken as the optimal switch state of the following sampling period, and the power semiconductor devices are switched accordingly.Fig. 9
The algorithm flow of FCS-MPCCFig. 10
FCS-MPCC control structure of the PV inverter

